# Excalidraw — Legacy Cursor Rules
# For modern rules, see .cursor/rules/*.mdc

## Project
- TypeScript/React monorepo with Yarn workspaces
- React 19, TypeScript 5.9 (strict), Vite 5, Vitest

## Architecture
- State: custom `actionManager` — NOT Redux/Zustand/MobX/Recoil
- Jotai used internally for per-instance isolation (`editor-jotai.ts`) — do not replace
- Rendering: Canvas via RoughJS — NOT react-konva/fabric.js/pixi.js
- Monorepo build order: common → math → element → excalidraw → excalidraw-app

## Code Style
- Functional components only, no classes
- TypeScript strict, no `any`
- PascalCase components, camelCase utilities
- Colocated tests (*.test.tsx) and styles (*.scss)
- Vitest for tests (not Jest)

## Constraints
- No new npm deps without approval
- No direct state mutation — use actionManager.dispatch()
- No modifications to restore.ts, manager.ts, types.ts without approval
- Check packages/utils/ and packages/common/ before adding helpers

## Commands
- `yarn install` — install deps
- `yarn build:packages` — build shared packages (run before app)
- `yarn start` — dev server on :3001
- `yarn test` — Vitest tests
- `yarn fix` — ESLint + Prettier

## Protected Files
- packages/excalidraw/data/restore.ts
- packages/excalidraw/actions/manager.ts
- packages/excalidraw/types.ts
- packages/element/src/types.ts
- packages/excalidraw/editor-jotai.ts
- packages/excalidraw/renderer/staticScene.ts
- packages/excalidraw/renderer/interactiveScene.ts
